  "text": "In summary, dietary fiber was inversely associated with insulin levels, weight gain, and other risk factors for CVD in young adults. The findings from this investigation, together with those of the Health Professionals' Follow-up Study, [CITATION_1] 25 raise the interesting possibility that fiber may play a greater role in determining CVD risk than total or saturated fat intake. Long-term interventional studies are needed to examine the effects of high-fiber and low glycemic index diets in the prevention of obesity and CVD.",
